<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="1128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1128">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/10–749: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary</gloss> to the
                            Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-07T15:00:00-05:00">October 7,
                                1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2051. Urtels 4211, 4217, October 7. Urgently request all facts concerning
                        release Isbrandtsen vessels and what conditions if any were imposed by Chi
                        Gov. Does <hi rend="italic">Flying Trader</hi> contemplate loading cargo and
                        passengers outbound passage Shanghai?</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>